author: Paul Wise
commit_message:
Adopt Python 3.9 argparse formatting change for zero-or-more args

Adopting it makes the output simpler and more user friendly and
fixes the test failures with Python 3.9.

This fixes the tests but not the regular output,
not sure of the appropriate way to fix the regular output,
as just using PlacFormatter causes the tests to fail.
Fixing the regular output too can happen at a later time.

Bug-Python: https://bugs.python.org/issue38438
Changed-in: https://github.com/python/cpython/commit/a0ed99bca8475cbc82e9202aa354faba2a4620f4

Use the same version of Python for plac_runner.py as the tests are run under

This ensures that when multiple Python versions are installed,
the right one is used when the plac runner is checking scripts.
